cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.SY

The paper discusses the use of neural networks to predict the performance of memory compilers, which involves electronic design automation (EDA) and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), which covers new and innovative approaches to EDA. The paper also involves computer architecture (cs.AR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) due to the use of neural networks. Additionally, it relates to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY) due to the optimization aspect of the work.
